						<summary>

						<p>On the pedestal of an image in the open air museum, Alampur.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Bhujabaḷamalla 12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This very much damaged and incomplete record belongs to the reign period of Kalachūri Bhujabalamalla. [Bhujabalamalla was one of the titles possessed by the Kalachēri king Bijjaḷa]. The purport of the record is not clear. Probably it registers a grant (of land), the details of which are lost and to the son (name lost) of Māramayya.</p>						

						</summary>
